<section xml:id="section-1-3" xmlns:xi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XInclude">
    <title>Limits</title>
    <p>
       For the P exam, you will need to recall the basic algebraic workings of limits, particularly at infinity.  
       Limits are also helpful in reviewing the definition of derivatives.  
       The more advanced topics regarding limits usually seen in calculus will not be covered here such has various convergence tests as they are not needed for the P exam.  
       We will cover a few dominance rules to provide some useful shortcuts.
    </p>

    <xi:include href="./subsection-1-3-1.ptx"/>
    <xi:include href="./subsection-1-3-2.ptx"/>
    <xi:include href="./subsection-1-3-3.ptx"/>
</section>